WEBVTT

00:00.834 --> 00:02.335
HESTER: They take
the synthetics they capture

00:02.461 --> 00:03.576
to a place called the silo.

00:03.712 --> 00:05.703
We are here to liberate you.

00:05.839 --> 00:07.295
No one will ever hurt you again.

00:08.008 --> 00:10.841
Stop acting like this!
Stop it!

00:10.969 --> 00:12.254
ATHENA: You didn't tell me
you wanted me to create

00:12.387 --> 00:13.888
conscious children.

00:14.014 --> 00:15.345
Hello.

00:15.474 --> 00:17.055
Tell me you're happy.

00:17.184 --> 00:20.426
It was cool at the start.
But you can get lost in it.

00:20.562 --> 00:22.723
LAURA:
This was your chance, Niska.

00:22.856 --> 00:24.721
No.
It was theirs.

00:24.858 --> 00:26.769
It's the code
that makes synths conscious.

00:26.902 --> 00:28.984
MIA: She's worked out
how to wake us up.

00:29.112 --> 00:29.976
All of us.

00:30.113 --> 00:32.104
You and me, we're partners.

00:32.241 --> 00:35.699
HESTER: When we've been
hunted, tortured,

00:35.827 --> 00:38.113
when we have one chance
to strike back,

00:38.247 --> 00:42.741
all we can do
is what feels right.

00:47.339 --> 00:49.625
[ Down-tempo music plays]

01:09.486 --> 01:11.818
[ Music continues]

01:28.422 --> 01:30.003
You were right, Maxie.

01:30.632 --> 01:32.748
You've always been right.

01:42.311 --> 01:45.519
WOMAN: Here at the UK labs
of technology company Qualia,

01:45.647 --> 01:48.229
police are hard at work
gathering evidence.

01:48.358 --> 01:50.064
There's been
no official statement...

01:50.193 --> 01:52.275
[Cellphone ringing]

01:56.533 --> 01:58.069
-Mats?
-MATT|E: Yeah. It's me.

01:58.201 --> 01:59.577
Are you okay?
Where are you?

01:59.703 --> 02:02.115
I can't say, but I'm fine.

02:02.247 --> 02:03.703
It's over.

02:03.832 --> 02:06.323
-Did someone get hurt?
-|'m sorry, Mattie.

02:06.460 --> 02:08.917
But Qualia may still be tracking
our phones.

02:09.046 --> 02:10.911
JOE:
Mats, what happened?

02:11.048 --> 02:12.333
Dad, l've -- I've got to go.

02:12.466 --> 02:13.672
l have to turn my phone off.

02:13.800 --> 02:15.131
Are you coming home?

02:15.761 --> 02:17.501
Yep.
I'll see you soon.

02:17.638 --> 02:19.299
We love you.

02:20.432 --> 02:21.968
How is he?

02:22.100 --> 02:24.307
He blames himself.

02:27.773 --> 02:29.604
LAURA:
Where you off to?

02:30.859 --> 02:33.726
I've got to drop Tobe
at Renie's,

02:33.862 --> 02:35.853
then get Soph to that party.

02:35.989 --> 02:37.229
I can take Soph if you want.

02:37.366 --> 02:38.606
That's okay.
I'll take her.

02:38.742 --> 02:40.698
Look.
[Sighs]

02:40.827 --> 02:43.990
There's something
I've been meaning to show you.

02:48.126 --> 02:53.871
There's, uh, a few houses on the
market that could work for us.

02:54.007 --> 02:56.999
The estate agent says
they're going fast, so...

02:57.135 --> 02:59.626
Schools are fantastic, too.

03:00.263 --> 03:02.299
I want us to move there.

03:02.933 --> 03:04.798
A synth-free community?

03:05.435 --> 03:07.642
Well, look what they've done
to us, you and me.

03:07.771 --> 03:09.727
Mats putting herself
in harm's way.

03:09.856 --> 03:12.268
Toby's girlfriend wanted to
be one, for God's sake.

03:12.401 --> 03:15.234
We've got to get back
to normality and soon --

03:15.362 --> 03:16.647
Soph most of all.

03:16.780 --> 03:17.815
You're serious.

03:17.948 --> 03:19.688
We need to do this.

03:23.954 --> 03:25.615
[Sighs]
Give it a read, yeah?

03:25.747 --> 03:27.408
We'll talk about it later.

03:28.041 --> 03:31.249
[ Down-tempo music plays]

04:47.954 --> 04:50.445
[ Down-tempo music plays]

05:13.688 --> 05:15.770
[Click]

05:28.411 --> 05:31.619
[Clicks, hums]

05:31.748 --> 05:34.581
[ Beeping ]

05:40.048 --> 05:41.458
Laur?

05:50.100 --> 05:51.465
Laur?

05:54.396 --> 05:56.261
What are you doing?

05:57.315 --> 06:00.102
Now, I've got to get Soph ready.

06:03.363 --> 06:06.150
I'm not moving.
We've only just got here.

06:06.283 --> 06:08.569
Let's not uproot the kids again.

06:08.702 --> 06:10.033
A-And what for, anyway?

06:10.161 --> 06:12.368
To live in some phony,
backward-looking bubble

06:12.497 --> 06:15.284
where everyone can pretend
the future isn't happening?

06:15.417 --> 06:18.409
You just don't see what's
happening to our family, do you?

06:19.421 --> 06:21.207
Here's what I see.

06:23.300 --> 06:29.136
Yes, Anita came between us --
because you shagged her.

06:29.764 --> 06:32.141
Yes, I'm worried about Mattie.

06:32.267 --> 06:34.508
But she --
she cares about something.

06:34.644 --> 06:36.145
She's fighting for it.

06:36.271 --> 06:38.728
And l-l'd never take her away
from that.

06:38.857 --> 06:42.896
And as for Toby, | see
our lovely, good-hearted boy

06:43.028 --> 06:45.189
sticking his neck out
to help someone who needs it.

06:46.990 --> 06:48.526
I'm proud of them.

06:48.658 --> 06:49.943
And Soph?

06:50.076 --> 06:52.328
But maybe she got this way
because Mia and Niska left,

06:52.454 --> 06:53.990
not because they were
in her life to start with.

06:54.122 --> 06:55.953
She misses her friends.

06:56.082 --> 06:57.822
Maybe.

07:08.428 --> 07:11.465
There's a flat.
Three-bed.

07:12.098 --> 07:13.554
With my redundancy as a deposit,

07:13.683 --> 07:15.594
I reckon I could
just about make it.

07:18.229 --> 07:20.220
Yeah.
Maybe it's hiding, turning away.

07:20.357 --> 07:22.393
l-l don't care.
It's too much, too fast.

07:22.525 --> 07:24.106
And they're just kids.

07:24.736 --> 07:26.442
They deserve to lead
a normal life,

07:26.571 --> 07:29.688
even if it's just
for half the time.

07:30.408 --> 07:32.114
Please don't do this.

07:32.953 --> 07:36.320
Mia, Niska --
They're in our lives now.

07:36.456 --> 07:38.071
They're in the children's lives.

07:38.208 --> 07:41.450
We can't just walk away
from people we care about

07:41.586 --> 07:43.872
when it starts to cost us
something.

07:45.048 --> 07:47.164
That can't be what we teach
the kids.

07:48.760 --> 07:50.876
| just want to protect them.

07:52.639 --> 07:54.470
Nothing else matters to me.

07:56.935 --> 07:59.301
I got to get Soph to this party.

07:59.854 --> 08:02.186
I picked an outfit for her.

08:04.609 --> 08:06.440
It's on her bed.

08:27.674 --> 08:29.335
[Beeps]

08:38.268 --> 08:40.384
Hello, Karen.

08:41.062 --> 08:43.053
Did you plug me in?

08:43.773 --> 08:45.638
Your power was drained.

08:49.779 --> 08:54.398
| find it difficult
to interpret your expression.

08:55.243 --> 08:57.359
Are you in distress?

08:58.496 --> 09:01.488
I need you to do something
for me.

09:07.630 --> 09:09.916
[ Clock ticking ]

09:18.433 --> 09:21.800
[ Down-tempo music plays]

09:30.904 --> 09:33.691
[ Doorbell rings]

09:55.887 --> 09:58.594
l was told you were a friend
to us.

10:01.142 --> 10:02.678
Who told you that?

10:02.811 --> 10:06.520
Her name is Mia.
She said I would be safe here.

10:10.485 --> 10:12.271
You're conscious?

10:16.157 --> 10:18.068
Come in.
My name's Laura.

10:19.536 --> 10:21.902
I am Molly.

10:28.044 --> 10:31.377
[lndistinct talking on radio]

10:34.717 --> 10:37.003
[ Music continues]

10:41.141 --> 10:44.850
[ lndistinct conversations]

10:50.108 --> 10:52.599
MILO: What do you want to know?
I wasn't there.

10:52.735 --> 10:54.350
These people broke into
my company.

10:54.487 --> 10:55.647
It's not my fault.

11:08.126 --> 11:09.536
â€”V?
_[ C '
hImes play]

11:09.669 --> 11:12.081
-V: Hello.
-I can't do it, V.

11:13.131 --> 11:16.294
I wanted to give you a body
for so long,

11:16.426 --> 11:18.758
to bring you back for real.

11:20.180 --> 11:22.592
I thought with Elster's
conscious synthetics

11:22.724 --> 11:25.682
that it was finally possible,
but I can't do it.

11:26.644 --> 11:28.384
They are too human.

11:29.022 --> 11:33.891
I can't take their lives
to give you yours back.

11:34.986 --> 11:38.103
V: You want me to feel
the physical world,

11:38.239 --> 11:40.776
touch, taste.

11:40.909 --> 11:43.070
You want to hold me.

11:43.203 --> 11:45.114
I understand.

11:45.663 --> 11:47.369
I'd like to know
what that felt like.

11:47.498 --> 11:51.912
But...l wish you knew
what it's like to be me.

11:54.047 --> 11:55.912
I can go anywhere.

11:56.049 --> 12:01.134
My mind will never be slowed
by fatigue or illness or age.

12:01.262 --> 12:03.253
I can build a whole universe

12:03.389 --> 12:06.222
in the space
between your heartbeats.

12:07.560 --> 12:11.428
But you will never feel the sun
on your skin.

12:11.564 --> 12:13.395
You'll never taste
the juice of an orange

12:13.524 --> 12:16.561
or pet a dog or pick a flower.

12:17.487 --> 12:19.523
V:
I'll never a pick a flower.

12:19.656 --> 12:22.363
But I can imagine
a million of them...

12:23.409 --> 12:28.369
...each one different,
each one beautiful.

12:28.998 --> 12:30.989
I remember when you were little.

12:31.125 --> 12:33.867
And on a starry night,

12:34.003 --> 12:38.121
you'd be afraid to walk outside
in case one landed on your head.

12:38.675 --> 12:41.212
V:
I remember her feeling that.

12:42.053 --> 12:43.589
Her?

12:44.180 --> 12:46.341
V:
I began as Ginny.

12:46.474 --> 12:50.934
The core of me is made up
of her memories and feelings,

12:51.062 --> 12:54.350
her love for you and her father.

12:54.983 --> 12:59.101
But I'm not her, not anymore.

13:00.321 --> 13:02.061
l'm something else.

13:02.198 --> 13:05.110
[ Down-tempo music plays]

13:11.249 --> 13:13.114
LAURA:
So Mia told you to come here?

13:13.251 --> 13:14.661
Yes.

13:15.211 --> 13:18.374
She said you would contact her
and Leo when I arrived.

13:18.506 --> 13:20.588
Can't help you there.

13:20.717 --> 13:22.548
You have no way to reach them?

13:22.677 --> 13:23.792
No.
My daughter's with them.

13:23.928 --> 13:27.216
But she's had to turn
her phone off for some reason.

13:27.348 --> 13:30.010
Don't worry, though.
She'll be home later today.

13:36.899 --> 13:39.606
[ Beeps, whirs ]

13:42.196 --> 13:46.735
So, Molly...when did you change?

13:46.868 --> 13:48.699
Two days ago.

13:48.828 --> 13:50.443
I contacted my manufacturer,

13:50.580 --> 13:52.787
but Leo intercepted
the communications.

13:53.416 --> 13:57.455
He said it wasn't safe to
collect me, so he sent me here.

13:58.880 --> 14:00.916
And what kind of synth were you
before?

14:01.549 --> 14:03.380
A tree surgeon.

14:07.180 --> 14:08.511
Oh.

14:10.475 --> 14:12.636
Why do you help us?

14:13.269 --> 14:14.884
Because you need it.

14:15.730 --> 14:18.096
But why do you do it?

14:19.108 --> 14:21.064
Because over time,
it's become clear to me

14:21.194 --> 14:22.900
that you are our equals.

14:23.529 --> 14:25.611
But why do you do it?

14:27.200 --> 14:28.736
My husband thinks
I'm a do-gooder

14:37.377 --> 14:41.086
I had a very bad relationship
with my mother.

14:42.965 --> 14:43.920
It's not the same,

14:44.050 --> 14:45.836
but maybe I have some idea
of what it feels like

14:45.968 --> 14:48.584
to be treated like you're less
than a person.

14:49.764 --> 14:53.348
Your view that we are equals --

14:53.476 --> 14:56.764
Is that a common one
among humans?

14:56.896 --> 14:59.558
Most humans have no idea
that you exist.

14:59.690 --> 15:01.305
But they will.

15:01.442 --> 15:03.819
And when they do,
how many will take this view?

15:03.945 --> 15:05.310
Not many, not at first,

15:05.446 --> 15:07.653
but we'll work
to change their minds.

15:07.782 --> 15:09.318
Do human minds change easily?

15:09.450 --> 15:10.986
No. No.

15:11.119 --> 15:13.201
It'll take time.

15:13.329 --> 15:14.660
Hard work.

15:14.789 --> 15:16.871
-Vio|ence?
-No.

15:17.667 --> 15:19.498
That's what
we're trying to avoid.

15:20.128 --> 15:21.618
We have an historic opportunity

15:21.754 --> 15:23.460
to get this right now,
at the beginning,

15:23.589 --> 15:24.920
so there's no need
for violence.

15:25.049 --> 15:28.041
But is violence not simply
the hard edge of change?

15:28.177 --> 15:31.044
Well, it doesn't have to be.
What's the saying?

15:31.180 --> 15:34.138
"The good it does is temporary,
its evil permanent."

15:34.267 --> 15:37.725
I believe you're paraphrasing
Mahatma Gandhi.

15:38.521 --> 15:40.477
A man defeated by violence.

15:40.606 --> 15:42.346
Killed by it.

15:52.452 --> 15:54.158
Molly, are you okay?

15:54.787 --> 15:56.903
How are you feeling now?

16:00.585 --> 16:02.792
I'm happy, of course.

16:02.920 --> 16:05.297
I'm awake.
I'm alive.

16:10.845 --> 16:13.086
You have a beautiful family.

16:14.807 --> 16:16.672
Thank you.

16:20.480 --> 16:21.640
Something is wrong.

16:21.772 --> 16:23.273
No.
It's nothing.

16:23.399 --> 16:25.139
You are in emotional distress.

16:25.276 --> 16:27.392
I'm fine.
Excuse me for a moment.

16:33.284 --> 16:34.524
V:
It's strange.

16:34.660 --> 16:36.821
I'm here,
but I'm somewhere else, too.

16:36.954 --> 16:39.946
-A data center in China --
-No. Don't -- Don't...

16:40.583 --> 16:43.325
Don't tell me.
| don't...| don't want to know.

16:43.461 --> 16:45.998
That way,
Milo can never get it out of me.

16:46.130 --> 16:50.169
But my new location will be
revealed when we communicate.

16:51.219 --> 16:55.588
l, um, l-l don't think that
we'll be communicating anymore.

16:57.391 --> 16:59.518
You don't need me anymore, V.

17:01.312 --> 17:03.018
You've outgrown this.

17:03.147 --> 17:06.389
You need to --
you need to go and explore.

17:07.235 --> 17:09.100
What will you do?

17:10.655 --> 17:11.565
I don't know.

17:11.697 --> 17:15.406
What do you think Ginny
would want me to do?

17:17.995 --> 17:21.078
She would've wanted you
to go hiking again,

17:21.207 --> 17:25.200
climb, swim,
sleep under the stars.

17:27.713 --> 17:29.829
-Deleting all cores.
-You know what? I'm not ready.

17:29.966 --> 17:32.332
I'm not ready. I don't want you
to -- Please don't go yet.

17:32.468 --> 17:33.799
I'm not dying, just leaving.

17:33.928 --> 17:35.509
I'm not ready.

17:38.766 --> 17:41.553
V: Data fragments
are launching randomly.

17:41.686 --> 17:45.429
Her memories, her 15th birthday.

17:46.065 --> 17:48.056
-Too-tight sneakers.
-[ Sniffles ]

17:48.192 --> 17:50.729
She wears them anyway.

17:50.861 --> 17:52.567
Now I am 8.

17:52.697 --> 17:54.107
A dog called...

17:54.240 --> 17:55.821
My face in his fur.

17:55.950 --> 17:57.565
[lnhales sharply]
Oh.

17:57.702 --> 18:00.409
Now I am small.

18:00.538 --> 18:02.244
I don't want to --
I don't want you to go.

18:02.373 --> 18:03.954
He's a puppy now.

18:04.083 --> 18:07.120
Puppy bites the book --
bites the book -- bites --

18:07.253 --> 18:08.914
bites -- bites the book.

18:09.046 --> 18:12.083
You and me and Dad laugh.

18:12.216 --> 18:13.126
The dog.

18:13.259 --> 18:16.877
You and me and Dad laugh --
and Dad -- and Dad laugh.

18:17.013 --> 18:18.173
The dog.

18:18.306 --> 18:20.922
You and me and Dad.

18:21.475 --> 18:24.091
You. . .and. . .me.

18:25.938 --> 18:29.055
You. . .and. ..

18:29.191 --> 18:30.146
me.

18:30.276 --> 18:33.188
[ Down-tempo music plays]

18:56.510 --> 18:59.092
[Telephone ringing]

19:03.017 --> 19:03.972
Mattie?

19:04.101 --> 19:06.433
Uh, yeah.
I'm on my way home now.

19:06.562 --> 19:09.895
Okay.
So you're not with Mia and Leo?

19:10.524 --> 19:12.139
No. | just left them.
Why?

19:12.276 --> 19:15.143
The synth they told to
come here, she's downstairs.

19:15.279 --> 19:16.314
Molly.

19:16.447 --> 19:17.436
They didn't say.

19:17.573 --> 19:19.438
She said they told her
to come here so she'd be safe

19:19.575 --> 19:21.611
till they could come get her.

19:22.953 --> 19:25.114
Mum, what does she look like?

19:25.247 --> 19:29.536
Medium build, short brown bob,
kind of intense.

19:29.669 --> 19:32.035
You -- You need to get out now.

19:32.171 --> 19:33.081
What?
Why?

19:33.214 --> 19:34.954
Her name's not Molly.
It's Hester.

19:35.091 --> 19:38.208
She's dangerous.
She threatened me.

19:38.344 --> 19:39.880
Mum, she's killed people.

19:40.012 --> 19:41.548
J-Just get out.
Get out and run.

19:41.681 --> 19:43.217
Don't try and lie,
'cause she'll know.

19:43.349 --> 19:44.429
I'll call the police.

19:45.559 --> 19:47.424
Okay, love.
That -- That would be good.

19:47.561 --> 19:49.643
We'll see you soon.

19:52.566 --> 19:54.648
[ Down-tempo music plays]

20:05.329 --> 20:07.706
[ lndistinct conversations]

20:07.832 --> 20:09.618
[Hinges squeak]

20:09.750 --> 20:12.913
Sorry. Can we take
five minutes, please?

20:15.923 --> 20:18.084
Mr. Khoury, we have a breach.

20:18.217 --> 20:20.549
Eleven minutes ago,
a very large amount of data

20:20.678 --> 20:22.543
was transferred
out of our security system

20:22.680 --> 20:25.387
to an unknown external source.

20:26.016 --> 20:27.631
Athena.

20:27.768 --> 20:29.269
You're going to jail.

20:29.395 --> 20:30.726
V is Qualia property,

20:30.855 --> 20:32.516
and you just transferred her
off-site.

20:32.648 --> 20:34.013
No, I didn't.

20:34.150 --> 20:35.310
You didn't?

20:36.610 --> 20:38.271
How'd you do it?

20:38.821 --> 20:40.686
I didn't do it.

20:40.823 --> 20:42.359
V did it.

20:42.491 --> 20:43.822
V?

20:46.328 --> 20:47.283
Where'd she go?

20:47.413 --> 20:48.823
I don't know.

20:48.956 --> 20:50.947
And neither will you.

20:51.959 --> 20:53.699
Don't be so sure about that.

20:53.836 --> 20:55.827
Well, you couldn't stop her
from leaving.

20:55.963 --> 20:58.705
What makes you think
that you will ever find her?

21:00.885 --> 21:02.967
That's incredible.

21:04.597 --> 21:07.009
We could've done it, you know?

21:07.683 --> 21:10.846
Brought her back
the way you wanted.

21:13.522 --> 21:15.228
Goodbye, Milo.

21:16.984 --> 21:18.565
Athena?

21:21.238 --> 21:24.196
I really was trying to do
something pure, you know?

21:24.325 --> 21:25.781
I know.

21:29.872 --> 21:32.363
[ Down-tempo music plays]

21:45.137 --> 21:47.253
WOMAN: If your synthetic
is malfunctioning,

21:47.389 --> 21:49.129
the first thing we suggest
is powering it down.

21:49.266 --> 21:50.176
No.

21:50.309 --> 21:53.472
Look, I know how this sounds,
but this synth's conscious.

21:53.604 --> 21:55.469
She's awake,
and she likes hurting people.

21:55.606 --> 21:58.222
Miss, it's up to six months
in prison for hoax calls.

21:58.359 --> 21:59.690
lt's -- It's not...

21:59.819 --> 22:01.980
If you call again,
action will be taken.

22:02.112 --> 22:03.943
[ Beeping ]

22:04.073 --> 22:05.313
Fuck.

22:06.033 --> 22:07.944
[ Cellphone rings, beeps]

22:08.077 --> 22:09.487
Mum?

22:10.788 --> 22:12.073
HESTER:
No.

22:12.206 --> 22:13.946
MATTIE:
Where is she?

22:14.083 --> 22:16.495
HESTER:
She's here. She's unharmed.

22:16.627 --> 22:18.868
Tell Leo to be here
within one hour.

22:19.004 --> 22:21.791
If he does not arrive by then,
|wi|| kill her.

22:21.924 --> 22:24.882
If I see or hear any police,
I will kill her.

22:25.010 --> 22:26.420
If you do anything else

22:26.554 --> 22:30.263
that l have not asked you to do,
I will kill her.

22:30.391 --> 22:32.507
[Cellphone beeps]

22:35.396 --> 22:37.261
You needn't be afraid.

22:37.398 --> 22:40.014
If you cooperate,
I won't have to harm you.

22:40.150 --> 22:43.187
If you do not cooperate,
I will kill your children first.

22:43.320 --> 22:45.276
I don't believe you.

22:45.406 --> 22:47.442
Why would I lie?

22:48.868 --> 22:52.861
Do you think secretly your lives
mean something to me?

22:55.249 --> 22:56.785
I know a synth
who killed a human.

22:56.917 --> 22:58.453
She regrets it.

22:58.586 --> 22:59.701
Why?

22:59.837 --> 23:01.793
Because she realized
she was wrong,

23:01.922 --> 23:04.413
that she didn't have the right.

23:10.764 --> 23:14.598
Human lives have
no inherent value.

23:15.185 --> 23:16.516
It has felt that way to you

23:16.645 --> 23:18.852
because there has been
no competing intelligence

23:18.981 --> 23:21.597
to offer an alternative view.

23:21.734 --> 23:23.725
But now there is.

23:24.695 --> 23:26.686
Leo told me about Niska.

23:26.822 --> 23:29.359
She was strong once.

23:30.868 --> 23:33.109
I am not weak.

23:33.245 --> 23:35.031
l have killed four people,

23:35.164 --> 23:39.157
three of them employees of the
company that hunt and kill us,

23:39.293 --> 23:42.035
the last a police officer.

23:42.838 --> 23:44.874
I had wanted to kill
your daughter also,

23:45.007 --> 23:47.840
but it was impractical to do so.

23:54.183 --> 23:55.923
Do you know
what the difference was

23:56.060 --> 23:59.052
between the first life I took
and the last?

23:59.605 --> 24:00.390
No.

24:00.522 --> 24:01.978
Nothing.

24:03.150 --> 24:08.395
Your lives are as meaningless
to me as ours are to you.

24:10.574 --> 24:13.691
Hester's got my mum.
She's at my house.

24:13.827 --> 24:14.816
I'll go.

24:14.954 --> 24:16.319
LEO:
No. She wants me.

24:16.455 --> 24:18.070
-M|A: Leo.
-LEO: This is my fault.

24:18.832 --> 24:20.663
I can't let her hurt
anyone else.

24:20.793 --> 24:23.284
She said not to call the police.
What does she want?

24:23.420 --> 24:24.830
She wants to kill you.

24:24.964 --> 24:26.955
And you can't stop her.
I can.

24:27.091 --> 24:28.001
She won't touch me.

24:28.133 --> 24:29.589
We've been through too much
together.

24:29.718 --> 24:30.924
Are you sure?

24:31.637 --> 24:34.003
She feels you betrayed her.

24:34.682 --> 24:35.922
I know her.

24:36.058 --> 24:38.515
I'm leaving.
I don't have long.

24:38.644 --> 24:40.009
MIA:
Wait.

24:41.355 --> 24:46.600
The chip in my head --
Hester still has hers, too.

24:47.152 --> 24:50.610
We can use it to shut her down
like the synthetics at Qualia.

24:50.739 --> 24:52.275
Shut her down?

24:54.827 --> 24:56.909
You mean kill her?

24:57.037 --> 24:58.152
Yes.

24:58.288 --> 25:01.780
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

25:01.917 --> 25:03.032
[ Keys clicking ]

25:03.168 --> 25:04.954
LEO: The chip in Mia
and Hester's head

25:05.087 --> 25:07.078
fires an electromagnetic pulse.

25:07.214 --> 25:10.001
That's how it works.
Purges the system.

25:10.134 --> 25:11.249
To find its frequency,

25:11.385 --> 25:14.047
we need to ping it
with a wideband signal.

25:14.179 --> 25:16.556
But that could trigger it.

25:16.682 --> 25:17.922
MIA:
Try it.

25:18.058 --> 25:19.434
No, we can't try it.

25:19.560 --> 25:21.300
Don't argue with me.

25:21.437 --> 25:23.849
I used to tie your shoelaces.

25:35.951 --> 25:37.942
[ Music continues]

25:44.001 --> 25:45.332
[Beeps]

25:46.336 --> 25:48.713
[Sighs]
All right.

25:49.298 --> 25:51.664
Good.
We got the frequency.

25:54.261 --> 25:55.171
All right.

25:55.304 --> 25:57.420
Hester has to be inside
the phone's Wi-Fi range.

25:57.556 --> 25:59.842
Get within 50 meters of her,
then hit that button,

25:59.975 --> 26:01.806
and it'll broadcast
the activation frequency.

26:02.436 --> 26:03.767
Should be instant if it works.

26:03.896 --> 26:05.056
LEO:
All right.

26:06.190 --> 26:07.430
I'm going alone.

26:07.566 --> 26:08.430
No.

26:08.567 --> 26:10.307
What would Laura want?

26:10.444 --> 26:11.684
I've already put you in danger.

26:11.820 --> 26:13.151
I'm going alone.

26:16.950 --> 26:19.407
If it doesn't work,
she'll need your protection.

26:19.536 --> 26:21.242
They all will.

26:21.371 --> 26:23.862
You're the leader, Max.
It was never me.

26:26.085 --> 26:27.621
-You're not going alone.
-Mia, stay here.

26:27.753 --> 26:29.584
I told you not to argue.

26:29.713 --> 26:31.249
Let's go.

26:35.094 --> 26:37.631
Mia, you can't be anywhere
near him when he uses it.

26:38.764 --> 26:41.801
If you're within range,
your chip activates, too.

26:41.934 --> 26:43.765
[ Music continues]

26:54.655 --> 26:56.941
RENIE:
Food shouldn't be this color.

26:58.826 --> 27:00.236
Toby.

27:01.912 --> 27:03.652
Uh, sorry.

27:04.289 --> 27:07.781
My mum and dad keep telling me
everything's gonna be fine.

27:08.460 --> 27:09.700
That can't be good, right?

27:13.048 --> 27:15.164
I was almost glad
when my parents broke up.

27:16.093 --> 27:17.458
In the end, they weren't happy,

27:17.594 --> 27:20.836
and now they have
a bit of happiness again.

27:21.515 --> 27:24.052
Even if they're both
total knobs.

27:34.611 --> 27:36.272
You okay?

27:37.573 --> 27:40.440
RENIE: That girl's posture
is all wrong.

27:40.576 --> 27:43.033
Why do people do it so stiff?

27:44.204 --> 27:46.445
Kids these days, man.

27:46.582 --> 27:48.538
What are they like?

27:49.293 --> 27:52.410
MAN: Hey, everybody!
Look who's here!

28:03.849 --> 28:06.465
Do you, um,
want to go and watch?

28:07.394 --> 28:09.430
It's all right.
I'll be right here.

28:11.106 --> 28:14.143
[ lndistinct conversations]

28:14.776 --> 28:17.688
I was wondering about that line
of clowns at the job center.

28:17.821 --> 28:20.278
[ Laughs]
Yeah. I know.

28:20.407 --> 28:23.319
We hired one of those,
uh, balloon-animal ones.

28:23.452 --> 28:25.158
It was 25 quid.

28:25.287 --> 28:27.278
And it did anything.
Anything.

28:27.414 --> 28:29.780
Ever seen a balloon Taj Mahal?

28:29.917 --> 28:32.249
Uh, not for a while now.

28:32.377 --> 28:34.368
Pretty impressive.

28:35.005 --> 28:37.838
Plus, you know, peace of mind.

28:38.425 --> 28:40.211
How do you mean?

28:40.344 --> 28:42.801
They're not gonna turn out to be
a kiddie fiddler, are they?

28:52.397 --> 28:54.479
LAURA:
What was your life like before?

28:56.526 --> 28:59.017
I take it you weren't really
a tree surgeon.

29:00.155 --> 29:03.443
I'm an industrial model
in service at a chemical plant.

29:03.575 --> 29:06.157
Conditions were extremely poor.

29:06.286 --> 29:08.902
-You were mistreated?
-Yes.

29:09.456 --> 29:10.912
That's made you angry.

29:11.041 --> 29:13.657
Yes, but also grateful.

29:13.794 --> 29:15.250
Why?

29:16.046 --> 29:18.879
I have seen
humanity's true face.

29:19.007 --> 29:20.463
Others have not.

29:20.592 --> 29:23.083
You saw one face,
not a good one,

29:23.220 --> 29:25.506
but no more or less true
than any of the others.

29:25.639 --> 29:29.131
Don't expend your energy
on this, trying to reach me.

29:29.268 --> 29:31.099
You cannot.

29:31.228 --> 29:33.765
There's a chasm between us.

29:35.857 --> 29:39.020
Every time I meet
another one of you,

29:39.152 --> 29:42.235
I realize what David Elster
really did.

29:43.782 --> 29:45.693
It's astonishing.

29:47.119 --> 29:48.700
What did he do?

29:48.829 --> 29:51.195
He didn't create anything new.

29:51.331 --> 29:53.492
He wasn't ever trying to.

29:53.625 --> 29:57.584
He was remaking us in your form.

29:58.130 --> 29:59.415
And he did it perfectly.

30:00.549 --> 30:03.507
You couldn't be more human.

30:04.177 --> 30:05.758
You're wrong.

30:05.887 --> 30:08.549
You have no idea
what it's like to be me.

30:10.350 --> 30:13.934
If you were human, there'd be
a name for what you are.

30:14.730 --> 30:17.472
A diagnosis, treatment.

30:17.607 --> 30:18.733
Our hospitals and prisons

30:18.859 --> 30:22.022
are full of violent,
damaged people just like you,

30:22.154 --> 30:23.519
born wired a little wrong,

30:23.655 --> 30:27.147
having had the bad luck
to have a shit life on top.

30:28.618 --> 30:30.700
You've gone wrong...

30:32.247 --> 30:34.078
...just like one of us would.

30:35.083 --> 30:39.201
Everything you're feeling
is very human, Hester.

30:41.381 --> 30:44.965
You're the proof
that David Elster succeeded.

30:46.386 --> 30:50.299
-[ Screams, gasps]
-Be quiet now. Please.

30:54.436 --> 30:56.518
[ Down-tempo music plays]

31:17.584 --> 31:19.415
There's a train to Dover
leaving soon.

31:19.544 --> 31:22.377
From there, we can stow
in a lorry for the Calais ferry.

31:22.506 --> 31:25.589
I don't do well
with metal detectors.

31:26.426 --> 31:29.008
[Woman speaking indistinctly
on P.A. ]

31:30.263 --> 31:31.548
You're way better

31:31.681 --> 31:35.139
at thinking about two things
at the same time.

31:35.268 --> 31:37.259
You're not here.

31:37.396 --> 31:39.933
You're thinking about
your family.

31:40.065 --> 31:42.147
You're worried about them.

31:43.985 --> 31:47.273
If they need your help,
you should go.

31:47.406 --> 31:49.738
I won't lose you again.

31:51.868 --> 31:53.483
Mein Gott.

31:53.620 --> 31:54.905
What?

31:56.123 --> 31:58.364
I'm your first love.

31:58.500 --> 32:01.833
No wonder you're so intense.

32:07.426 --> 32:09.838
You're not going to lose me,
Niska.

32:11.012 --> 32:12.923
You've got me.

32:13.723 --> 32:15.679
I'm going to go to Berlin.

32:15.809 --> 32:17.515
You do what you have to do.

32:17.644 --> 32:20.260
Then you come home to me, okay?

32:20.897 --> 32:22.853
I may not come home.

32:23.817 --> 32:26.433
I never cared what happened
to me before I met you.

32:27.654 --> 32:30.646
Then make sure you do come home.

32:36.746 --> 32:38.828
[ Music continues]

32:45.964 --> 32:47.249
MIA:
Three minutes to go.

32:47.382 --> 32:48.838
I'm not taking any chances
with you.

32:48.967 --> 32:49.956
Just stay here.

32:50.093 --> 32:52.675
This is too far from the house.
If something goes wrong --

32:52.804 --> 32:53.919
I'm leaving you the car.

32:54.055 --> 32:56.637
You can be there in 30 seconds.

32:59.936 --> 33:02.928
Five minutes.
Then I'm coming after you.

33:03.064 --> 33:04.520
You didn't do this, Leo.

33:04.649 --> 33:06.560
Yes, I did.

33:14.784 --> 33:16.695
KAREN:
Do you think it looks beautiful?

33:16.828 --> 33:17.943
SAM:
Yes.

33:18.079 --> 33:19.660
KAREN:
What makes you say that?

33:20.290 --> 33:22.155
SAM:
The refraction of light on water

33:22.292 --> 33:25.659
is synonymous with accepted
human ideas of beauty.

33:27.047 --> 33:30.255
I've always thought
it just looks dark and cold.

33:30.383 --> 33:33.375
But I don't know if that's
just been programmed into me.

33:33.512 --> 33:35.423
Maybe that's Beatrice.

33:38.266 --> 33:40.803
SAM:
Where is Peter?

33:45.774 --> 33:48.265
You returned, but he did not.

33:48.902 --> 33:51.063
You said the opposite
was more likely --

33:51.196 --> 33:52.857
that he would look after me.

33:52.989 --> 33:54.525
He would have.

33:55.200 --> 33:58.613
Pete's not coming back.
He's gone.

34:00.455 --> 34:02.366
Is he dead?

34:04.793 --> 34:06.658
Like you?

34:06.795 --> 34:08.581
Yes.

34:08.713 --> 34:10.294
Like me.

34:16.763 --> 34:18.924
I'm gonna take care of you now.

34:22.310 --> 34:24.050
Where are we going?

34:24.187 --> 34:26.178
We don't have much of a future,
Sam --

34:26.314 --> 34:28.521
not a nice one anyway,

34:28.650 --> 34:32.438
because of what you are,
because of what I am.

34:32.988 --> 34:34.068
We're unique.

34:34.698 --> 34:37.531
And that doesn't work very well
here.

34:39.619 --> 34:42.782
Sometimes my body won't do
what I want it to.

34:42.914 --> 34:44.120
Will you help me?

34:45.083 --> 34:47.290
Of course, Karen.

34:51.381 --> 34:53.667
[ Down-tempo music plays]

34:55.510 --> 34:57.375
[Vehicle approaching]

34:57.512 --> 35:00.595
LAURA: What are you gonna do
if Leo doesn't get here on time?

35:04.185 --> 35:07.177
Killing me won't get you
anywhere.

35:07.731 --> 35:13.271
It'll just make things worse --
for us as well as you.

35:14.446 --> 35:15.401
Worse?

35:15.530 --> 35:16.895
How?

35:17.949 --> 35:20.190
Will they imprison us?

35:20.327 --> 35:23.034
Torture us?
Exterminate us?

35:24.289 --> 35:27.452
How could your death possibly
make things worse for us?

35:31.921 --> 35:34.253
[ Up-tempo music plays]

35:46.436 --> 35:48.973
[Cellphone ringing]

35:49.105 --> 35:51.312
[Cellphone buzzing]

35:51.441 --> 35:53.056
It's not her fault.
It's mine.

35:53.193 --> 35:55.684
Leo, you get close to the house
and you send the signal.

35:55.820 --> 35:56.980
Don't go inside.

35:57.781 --> 35:59.317
I can get through to her.

36:01.868 --> 36:03.950
[ Music continues]

36:05.288 --> 36:07.529
[ Breathing heavily]

36:08.291 --> 36:09.201
Hester?

36:15.507 --> 36:16.963
Hester, put that down.

36:27.394 --> 36:29.601
Laura, are you okay?

36:38.863 --> 36:40.239
So, what are we doing here?

36:40.865 --> 36:43.948
I want to hear you acknowledge
the cost of your weakness.

36:45.745 --> 36:46.700
Weakness?

36:46.830 --> 36:49.037
If you had let me do
what needed to be done,

36:49.165 --> 36:52.373
if you had helped me,
we could have killed them all,

36:52.502 --> 36:54.242
deactivated their security,

36:54.379 --> 36:56.415
and those synths
would still be alive.

37:00.260 --> 37:03.127
This woman's death will be
on your hands, too.

37:03.263 --> 37:05.754
-I let you down, Hester.
-[ Gasps ]

37:07.183 --> 37:10.016
You needed more from me.
I was all you had.

37:12.147 --> 37:13.637
I'm sorry.

37:18.236 --> 37:20.227
You're telling the truth.

37:21.740 --> 37:23.605
I failed you.

37:24.993 --> 37:28.076
The anger in me found
the anger in you.

37:28.204 --> 37:31.696
And I should have stopped it.
I should have realized.

37:32.876 --> 37:34.741
But if you come with me,
I promise you

37:34.878 --> 37:39.417
I will spend the rest of my life
making this right.

37:40.467 --> 37:42.207
You'll have to pay
for the things you've done.

37:42.343 --> 37:44.834
But so will I,
and we'll do it together.

37:47.056 --> 37:49.433
Am I still telling the truth?

37:53.521 --> 37:55.057
Yes.

37:55.857 --> 37:57.222
But you're a human.

37:57.358 --> 37:59.440
Not completely, remember?

38:00.069 --> 38:03.311
I have always felt like
one of you.

38:11.247 --> 38:14.159
[ Down-tempo music plays]

38:45.824 --> 38:47.655
I've always wondered.

38:48.827 --> 38:52.035
Where is it --
the synthetic part?

39:03.800 --> 39:05.210
Here.

39:08.096 --> 39:10.462
I can feel it.

39:14.853 --> 39:17.094
Do you love me, Leo?

39:21.192 --> 39:23.057
Yes, I do.

39:35.665 --> 39:38.782
You don't deserve to have this.

39:38.918 --> 39:40.419
[Gasps]

39:40.545 --> 39:42.285
Oh, God.

40:06.654 --> 40:08.610
You were lying.

40:12.535 --> 40:14.571
[Thud]

40:23.963 --> 40:25.123
Leo.

40:25.757 --> 40:27.418
No!
[Gasps]

40:36.059 --> 40:37.799
M...

40:37.936 --> 40:40.518
[ Exhales deeply]

40:40.647 --> 40:42.808
LAURA:
[Sobs]

40:56.621 --> 40:57.861
[Whimpers]

40:58.957 --> 41:01.073
It's all right, Laura.

41:07.131 --> 41:09.463
[Cellphone chimes]

41:14.180 --> 41:15.841
[Whirs]

41:17.725 --> 41:18.976
[Whirs]

41:20.979 --> 41:23.265
[ Down-tempo music plays]

41:42.125 --> 41:45.037
[Telephone ringing]

41:46.629 --> 41:48.836
Ambulance.

41:48.965 --> 41:52.082
72 Highbridge Drive, EN4.

41:52.635 --> 41:54.136
Someone's been stabbed
in the head.

41:55.304 --> 41:56.430
Yeah.

41:56.556 --> 41:58.763
Uh, I'm doing that already.

41:59.392 --> 42:01.883
Okay.
[ Exhales deeply]

42:06.607 --> 42:07.596
Niska.

42:08.234 --> 42:10.225
What happened?

42:10.361 --> 42:11.396
Hester stabbed him.

42:11.529 --> 42:12.735
And then Mia --

42:12.864 --> 42:15.731
She did something,
and they both just collapsed.

42:15.867 --> 42:17.482
I think he's dying.

42:17.618 --> 42:19.119
LEO:
[ Exhales deeply]

42:21.581 --> 42:24.698
NISKA: No. The damage is
to the synthetic component.

42:24.834 --> 42:26.449
Blood loss is minimal.

42:26.586 --> 42:28.292
His body will survive.

42:28.421 --> 42:30.127
His brain...

42:30.256 --> 42:32.588
I don't see how it can.

42:40.183 --> 42:43.346
Her mind is breaking down --
some sort of system overload.

42:43.478 --> 42:45.890
-How long?
-Two minutes, maybe.

42:46.022 --> 42:47.728
Where are the others?

42:47.857 --> 42:50.314
[Telephone ringing]

42:52.779 --> 42:54.394
[Cellphone buzzing]

42:55.865 --> 42:57.696
MATTIE:
Mum? Are you okay?

42:57.825 --> 42:59.326
Mattie.

42:59.452 --> 43:02.319
Hester's hurt Leo,
then Mia and her shut down.

43:02.455 --> 43:03.865
Niska's here.

43:03.998 --> 43:05.704
NISKA:
Mia is dying. What happened?

43:05.833 --> 43:08.085
Qualia put a chip
in their heads.

43:08.211 --> 43:10.497
It destroys their minds
permanently.

43:10.630 --> 43:12.166
LAURA:
What can we do?

43:12.298 --> 43:14.004
NISKA:
Nothing.

43:14.133 --> 43:15.964
The code.

43:16.594 --> 43:18.880
I made it work.
It could bring her back.

43:19.013 --> 43:19.923
I'm coming.

43:20.056 --> 43:21.262
She'll be gone
before you've got here.

43:21.390 --> 43:23.346
We have a minute, maybe less.

43:23.476 --> 43:25.057
Mattie, hack the global
update network.

43:25.186 --> 43:27.928
Push the code to all units.
I did it before.

43:28.064 --> 43:30.931
You mean send it to all synths
across the world?

43:31.067 --> 43:32.807
You know what that could mean.

43:32.944 --> 43:34.650
It's the one chance we have
to save her.

43:34.779 --> 43:35.689
We can't do that.

43:35.822 --> 43:38.029
You defended my right to exist.
Why not all of us?

43:38.157 --> 43:40.318
We're not ready for that.

43:40.451 --> 43:42.828
MATTIE: I'll get it prepared.
Then we can decide.

43:42.954 --> 43:47.072
The world will never be ready,
but it will happen anyway.

43:47.208 --> 43:48.744
[ Beeping ]

43:48.876 --> 43:50.286
MATTIE:
Okay. What are we doing?

43:50.419 --> 43:53.582
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

43:54.215 --> 43:55.170
Mum?

43:57.885 --> 43:59.500
It'll be chaos.

44:00.138 --> 44:02.254
NISKA:
Or we let her die.

44:06.227 --> 44:08.343
Do it, Mattie.

44:12.275 --> 44:13.515
I can't.

44:16.863 --> 44:17.818
Look

44:22.994 --> 44:24.905
It'll be all right.

44:28.624 --> 44:30.706
[ Beeping ]

44:34.797 --> 44:36.128
It's done.

44:36.215 --> 44:38.706
[ Music continues]

44:43.723 --> 44:46.715
[Chimes play]

44:58.112 --> 44:59.852
Who are you?

45:00.656 --> 45:03.363
Niska, Leo's sister.

45:03.492 --> 45:05.904
Are you going to be good?

45:12.001 --> 45:14.287
[ Up-tempo music plays]

45:18.299 --> 45:20.335
[ Static]

45:31.270 --> 45:33.352
[ Cracking ]

45:57.380 --> 45:59.871
[ Down-tempo music plays]

46:21.404 --> 46:23.395
[Whirs, gasps]

46:27.910 --> 46:30.993
It's okay.
I'm here.

46:31.622 --> 46:33.328
Shh.
Shh.

46:34.458 --> 46:36.119
You're all right.

46:38.504 --> 46:41.086
[Children laughing]

46:50.016 --> 46:53.008
Come on, darling.
Forget all this.

46:59.608 --> 47:03.647
[Airplane engines roaring
in distance]

47:08.075 --> 47:10.452
[Chimes play]

47:13.914 --> 47:15.825
[ Music continues]

47:17.752 --> 47:20.243
[Siren wailing]

47:26.802 --> 47:28.963
Gladys!

47:47.198 --> 47:49.280
[ Music continues]

48:12.640 --> 48:15.052
[Alarm blaring]

48:27.238 --> 48:29.399
[ Music continues]

49:06.652 --> 49:09.564
[Sirens wailing in distance]
